.
他曾说，“等病好了，还上一线，不想当逃兵。
He said, "When I get well, I'm still on the line and I don't want to be a deserter.
”2月7日中午13:02，中央纪委国家监委网站发布消息，经中央批准，国家监察委员会决定派出调查组赴湖北省武汉市，就群众反映的涉及李文亮医生的有关问题作全面调查。
On February 7, at 13: 02 noon, the website of the National Monitoring Committee of the Central Committee on Discipline announced that, with the approval of the central government, the State Supervision Committee decided to send an investigation team to Wuhan, Hubei Province, to make a comprehensive investigation into the questions raised by the masses concerning Dr. Li Wenliang.
2月6日深夜，李文亮生命垂危的消息传来，亿万网友彻夜难眠。
Late at night on February 6, Li Wenliang was dying news, hundreds of millions of netizens sleepless all night.
《中国新闻周刊》于当晚22时24分打通武汉市中心医院重症监护室电话，对方表示李文亮正在接受抢救。
China News Weekly opened the intensive care unit of Wuhan Central Hospital at 2224 hours that evening, saying Li was receiving emergency treatment.
武汉协和医院一名医生表示，李文亮于当晚21时30分左右停止了心跳，后来一直使用ECMO（人工膜肺）进行抢救。
A doctor at Wuhan Concorde Hospital said Li stopped beating around 21: 30 pm and later used ECMO to rescue him.
2月7日3点48分，武汉市中心医院官方微博发布消息称，该院眼科医生李文亮，在抗击新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情工作中不幸感染，经全力抢救无效，于2020年2月7日凌晨2点58分去世，对此我们深表痛惜和哀悼。
At 3: 48 a.m. on February 7, the official Weibo of Wuhan Central Hospital announced that Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at Wuhan City Central Hospital, died on February 7, 2020 at 2.58 a.m. after a desperate attempt to rescue him from the pneumonia epidemic that infected the coronavirus.
1月31日，《中国新闻周刊》曾在线采访了还在重症监护室接受治疗的李文亮。
On January 31, China Newsweek interviewed Li Wenliang, who is still in intensive care.
他由于插管呼吸，无法说话，只能打字和外界交流。
He was unable to speak due to intubation and could only type and communicate with the outside world.
当时，医生告诉他，病情的拐点就在这几天了，但肺功能恢复还需要一段时间，他说，“等病好了，还上一线，不想当逃兵。
At the time, the doctor told him that the point of inflection was only a few days away, but it would take some time for his lungs to function again, he said.
”李文亮生前曾因在微信群发出警示“华南水果海鲜市场确诊了7例SARS”而遭到公安部门的训诫。
Li Wenliang was reprimanded by the public security department for issuing warnings in small letters that "seven cases of SARS were confirmed in the South China fruit and seafood market."
在文字回复过程中，李文亮多次暂停采访，接受治疗。
In the text response process, Li Wenliang repeatedly suspended the interview, accepted the treatment.
“不好意思，刚才在打针，用了抗生素，血象有点高，可能是合并细菌感染。
"I'm sorry, I just had an injection, antibiotics, a little high blood, maybe a combination of bacterial infection.
”在一次二十多分钟的中断后，李文亮回复道。
After a break of more than 20 minutes, Mr Li replied.
李文亮，辽宁人，今年34岁。
Li Wenliang, from Liaoning Province, is 34 years old.
他说，在2004年高考后，因不太喜欢熟人社会与人情世故，决定去南方上大学。
After the 2004 college entrance examination, he said, he decided to go to college in the south because he didn't like the social and cultural sophistication of acquaintances.
出于就业比较稳定的考虑，他报考了武汉大学临床医学七年制专业。
Due to stable employment considerations, he applied for the Wuhan University Clinical Medicine seven-year major.
毕业后，他曾在厦门工作了三年，2014年回到武汉，在武汉市中心医院眼科工作至今。
After graduation, he worked in Xiamen for three years, in 2014 returned to Wuhan, Wuhan City Central Hospital ophthalmology work to date.
2019年12月30日，李文亮听同事说，急诊科隔离了7名来自于华南海鲜市场的SARS病人。
On December 30, 2019, Mr. Lee heard from colleagues that the emergency department had quarantined seven SARS patients from the South China seafood market.
当天下午5点多，他在150多人的大学同学群里发了这一消息，又解释说“SARS的表述不太准确，应该是冠状病毒，具体分型还有待确认”，让大家加强防范，并强调不要外传。
The SARS coronavirus (coronavirus) is a coronavirus, but the coronavirus is a coronavirus, and the coronavirus has been confirmed.
然而，这张“华南海鲜市场确诊7例SARS”的微信截图还是流传了出来，在网上大量转发。
However, this "South China Seafood Market confirmed 7 cases of SARS" micro-screenshot or spread out on the Internet a large number of forwarding.
看到被“断章取义”地截图，还不打码，李文亮一开始也有些生气，预感自己可能会被处罚，但随后马上就释然了，别人可能也是一时着急，和他一样，也是出于提醒家人朋友的目的。
Li Wenliang was a little angry at first and had a presentiment that he might be punished, but then he was relieved. Others may have been in a moment of anxiety, just like him, to remind family and friends.
12月31日凌晨1点半，李文亮接到电话，要求其去武汉市卫健委。
On December 31 at 1: 30 a.m., Li Wenliang received a telephone call to Wuhan city health committee.
“当时卫健委连夜开会，应该是应对疫情的会议，我们医院院领导、医务室主任都参加了。
"At that time, Wei Jiansheng night meeting, should be to deal with the epidemic situation, our hospital leadership, the director of the infirmary all attended.
”会议结束后，院领导询问了李文亮消息来源，于凌晨4点多送他回家。
"After the meeting, the hospital leadership questioned Li Wenliang's sources and sent him home at 4 a.m.
到了白天，李文亮又去了两三次医院监察科，反复被询问消息来源以及是否认识到“造谣的错误”，并要求其写一份“不实消息外传”的反思与自我批评。
During the day, Li went to the hospital's inspection section two or three times and was repeatedly asked about the source of the information and whether he realized the "falsehood" and asked to write a reflection and self-criticism of the "false news spread."
就在31日当天，一份盖有武汉市卫健委公章的红头文件在社交媒体上流出，文件紧急通知“武汉市华南海鲜市场陆续出现不明原因肺炎”，这一天下午，武汉市卫健委发布通报称，“近期部分医疗机构发现接诊的多例肺炎病例与华南海鲜城有关联，已发现27例病例，其中7例病情严重”，并指出，“未发现明显人传人现象，未发现医务人员感染。
On the 31st, a red paper bearing the official seal of Wuhan Municipal Healthy Commissary flowed on social media, and the document urgently announced that "unknown pneumonia has appeared in south China seafood market in Wuhan," Wuhan Health Commission said on the afternoon of that day.
”李文亮回忆说，自己当时想着不被拘留就好，便签了字。
"I was thinking of not being detained, so I signed," he recalls.
之后，医院科室主任口头传达不要在网络上发布相关信息。
Afterwards, the hospital department director verbally conveys does not publish the relevant information on the network.
1月8日那天，李文亮接诊了一位82岁急性闭角型青光眼女性患者。
On January 8, Li Wenliang attended an 82-year-old woman with acute angle-closure glaucoma.
患者当时没有发热症状，他就没询问对方是否有华南海鲜市场接触史。
The patient did not have febrile symptoms, he did not ask each other whether there is a history of exposure to the South China seafood market.
第二天，该患者食欲不振，开始发热，检查肺部CT显示“双肺磨玻璃样病变”，由当时没有核酸试剂盒，排除了常见病毒感染，支原体、衣原体感染后，医生只能“高度怀疑她是不明原因肺炎”。
The next day, the patient was suffering from loss of appetite, began febrile, and CT scan of the lungs showed "double lung grinds glassy lesions," by the absence of nucleic acid test kits at the time, ruling out common viral infections, and after mycoplasma and chlamydia infections, doctors could only "highly suspect she was pneumonia of unknown cause."
9日晚，照顾该患者的家属也出现发热，这是明显的人传人现象，三天后，患者被转到了呼吸内科隔离病房。
On the evening of the 9th, the family members who took care of the patient also developed fever, which was an obvious human-to-human phenomenon. Three days later, the patient was transferred to the respiratory isolation ward.
李文亮也很快出现了症状，1月10日开始咳嗽，11日早起后量体温显示38.2度，意识到情况不对，李文亮马上搬到酒店隔离，远离孕中的妻子和孩子，并在医院查了CT，显示双肺多发感染，磨玻璃样病变。
Realizing that the situation was wrong, Li Wenliang immediately moved to the hotel to be isolated, away from his wife and children, and checked the CT scan at the hospital, showing multiple lung infections and grinding glass-like lesions.
12日下午，李文亮搬到科室病房，14日转到医院呼吸科隔离，据他回忆，还有另外两位眼科同事在他之后也被感染，同事们自此开始自觉戴上N95口罩了。
On the afternoon of December 12, Mr. Li moved to the hospital's respiratory ward, where he was transferred to respiratory isolation on the 14th. He recalled that two other ophthalmologists had also been infected after him.
到呼吸科隔离治疗两天后，李文亮出现呼吸困难加重的情况，并在24日转到重症监护室，使用抗生素、激素、抗病毒类药物和高流量吸氧治疗，24日当天做的核酸检测一直没有收到结果。
After two days of isolation in the respiratory department, Li Wenliang developed dyspnea and was transferred to intensive care unit on the 24th, using antibiotics, hormones, antiviral drugs and high-flow oxygen therapy.
1月28日，李文亮转移到呼吸内科重症监护室四天后终于做了核酸检测，“30号的时候，（主治）医生告诉我，核酸显示为阴性”。
On January 28, Li Wenliang was transferred to the intensive care unit of the Department of Respiratory Medicine for a nucleic acid test. "At 30, the doctor told me the nucleic acid was negative.
2月1日，李文亮的核酸检测结果为阳性。
On February 1, Li Wenliang tested positive for nucleic acid.
李文亮医生微博截图在李文亮感染两天后，他的父母也出现发热、呕吐的症状，CT检查出典型的“磨玻璃样病变”，他回忆，大概在1月15、16日，老两口住进了医院，当时医院床位已经很紧张了，好在两位老人病症较轻，预计很快就能出院，“我不太担心，他们住院离家很近，走回家20分钟左右。
Two days after his infection, his parents also developed symptoms of fever and vomiting. The CT scan showed a typical "grinded glass-like lesion." On January 15 or 16, the old couple were admitted to the hospital.
”李文亮回复道，他当时不敢和父母多说自己的情况，怕他们担心。
Mr Li replied that he did not dare to tell his parents much about himself for fear that they would worry.
作为武汉的一名普通医生，李文亮的去世引起人们强烈的惋惜之情。
As an ordinary doctor in Wuhan, the death of Li Wenliang caused strong feelings of regret.
随着新冠肺炎疫情正在扩散并对社会造成难以弥补的损失，他生前的勇敢行为更是受到普遍的赞扬。
As the outbreak of pneumonia spread and caused irreparable damage to society, his brave actions during his lifetime were widely praised.
李文亮是一个热爱生活的人，他的微信头像是蜡笔小新画风的一家四口，微博里的他也是跟蜡笔小新爸爸一样的风格，生日夜为吃到鸡腿而开心，并自嘲“买不起车厘子”。
Li Wenliang is a life-loving person, his micro-letter head is crayon xiao xin style of a family of four, micro-blogging he is the same style as the new father crayon, living day and night happy to eat chicken legs, and self-mocking "can not afford to buy a car."
图为李文亮医生微信头像躺在病床上的李文亮还在时刻关注一线医护人员物资短缺的情况，“我们医院也缺，”李文亮1月31日回复道，据他所知，他所在医院的一线医护人员经常8小时才轮一次班，很多人会在防护服里穿尿不湿，当时被感染住院的医护人员可能有五六十人。
Li Wenliang, lying on his sickbed, is still concerned about the shortage of supplies for front-line medical staff. "We are short of hospital staff," Li replied on January 31.
